    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a premium offensive outlook, anchored by **Corbin Carroll** (87.14) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75). **Corbin Carroll** is our clear top play; facing Taijuan Walker (4.79 xERA), his elite sprint speed is boosted by an advantageous order spot and a favorable park factor, making him a prime candidate for a multi-category eruption. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** benefits immensely from the matchup against Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez. The combination of M\u00e1rquez\u2019s 5.26 xERA, wind blowing out, and a slow delivery that projects well for our SB-scarcity mandate pushes **Mickey Moniak** into the top tier of our starting nine. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) rounds out our elite grouping, capitalizing on a soft matchup against Erick Fedde to maximize his counting stat potential.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's card was bypassing **Trevor Story** (49.25) in favor of middle-tier starters like **Alex Freeland** and **Max Muncy**. While **Trevor Story** carries pedigree, the projected efficiency metrics favor **Alex Freeland** due to the specific SP skill gap, even with the latter batting in the #8 hole. **Jose Caballero** (48.89) was the next man out, narrowly edged by our active MI options. We remain cautious regarding **James Wood** (62.67), whose score is supported by a lead-off spot but challenged by a neutral-to-difficult platoon against Harrison. We are monitoring lineup confirmations closely for **Josh Naylor** and **Tyler Soderstrom**; while both are projected to start in the heart of the order, any unforeseen defensive shifts or rest days will force immediate adjustments to our game-cap management.",
